episodes.title: You're the Indian Now
episodes.plot: In the wake of the Beck Brothers, John reshuffles the political decks; Beth finds a trespasser on the ranch and learns that he may have big ambitions for the surrounding land; John helps Tate deal with his nightmares.

episodes.title: Freight Trains and Monsters
episodes.plot: Jamie starts a new job; Beth comes to a realization about Market Equities and visits Roarke; Rip searches for another ranch hand: A livestock agent goes too far.

episodes.title: An Acceptable Surrender
episodes.plot: Jamie plays cover-up and damage control with Hendon; Governor Perry hears a $6 billion pitch for a development right on the Yellowstone, and later makes some political maneuvers; Jimmy competes in a rodeo competition.

episodes.title: Going Back to Cali
episodes.plot: Beth shares a personal secret with Rip; John and the boys deal with some hostile trespassers from out of state; Rainwater reaches out to a powerful woman to help secure the future of Broken Rock.

episodes.title: Cowboys and Dreamers
episodes.plot: The reason for Beth and Jamie's toxic relationship is revealed. Kayce bends the rules to help a family in need. Rip and the boys get into a confrontation with two men from John's past.

episodes.title: All for Nothing
episodes.plot: Beth reveals a secret to her father; John confronts two cowboys about old feuds; a search gets underway on the reservation.

episodes.title: The Beating
episodes.plot: Kayce searches for answers following a theft on the ranch, Jamie learns a shocking family secret, John issues a warning, and Beth takes matters into her own hands.

episodes.title: I Killed a Man Today
episodes.plot: Beth continues her battle with Willa Hayes, and brings John a lucrative offer. Monica has a harrowing ordeal.

episodes.title: Meaner Than Evil
episodes.plot: Jamie confronts his past. Rip approaches Kayce about an old problem. The bunkhouse looks to defend two of their own.

episodes.title: The World Is Purple
episodes.plot: John sits down at the negotiating table with former friends and foes. As the battle for the future of the Yellowstone heats up, nothing will ever be the same.
